snippet.textDisplay:
We shouldn't be comparing the UK to other countries because in reality we have no clear idea of which 'stage' we are really at. Unlike most countries we are only testing people who are critically ill and who have to come into hospital as a last resort. Therefore of course it would appear that a higher proportion are dying per number of people tested - as the people being tested are on the brink of death.

I usually think the BBC does a good job, but this seems to be quite a bit of fear mongering. However, at a time where people are still going outside like nothings wrong maybe this scare factor is what we need.
